#=GF RT   A gene encoding a DUF523 domain protein is involved in the
#=GF RT   conversion of 2-thiouracil into uracil.
#=GF RA   Aucynaite A, Rutkiene R, Gasparaviciute R, Meskys R,
#=GF RA   Urbonavicius J;
#=GF RL   Environ Microbiol Rep. 2018;10:49-56.
#=GF DR   INTERPRO; IPR007553;
#=GF DR   SO; 0100021; polypeptide_conserved_region;
#=GF CC   This family of proteins, predominantly found in Bacteria, are
#=GF CC   involved in the desulfuration of 2-thiouracil into uracil in the
#=GF CC   2-thiouridine degradation pathway. It has been demonstrated that
#=GF CC   these proteins contain a Fe-S cluster required for their
#=GF CC   activity [1].
